editorialSummary.text: Department of the Walgreens chain providing prescription medications & other health-related items.

originalText.text: I am not sure what people are saying here and each have their own experiences but these ladies were super friendly, funny and helpful. They got my prescription filled in like a minute. Would definitely recommend this store.

originalText.text: Do not even bother with this place, it is almost comically bad in regards to the customer service and amount of time you will wait around. It was like a three ring circus today waiting to pick up a prescription. Literally seven staff members milling around behind the registers and in the prescription-filling area and no one was addressing the customers.  Then people are laughing and acting like they are in middle school trying to figure out how to pull up someone's record... complete clownery all around.  Better to just walk to another pharmacy instead and retain a shred of your sanity.

originalText.text: This particular store and its' pharmacy associates have somehow managed to take the compassion and humanity out of healthcare medicine. Every time i have to come in because of an urgent issue i regret not making other choices, forgetting the alternatives just 2-3 blocks in any other direction.
